algorithms: Contains configuration options specific to the algorithm used during indexing or querying.
name: The name to associate with this algorithm configuration.
kind: The algorithm kind. HNSW is approximate; Exhaustive KNN is exact.
metric: The similarity metric to use for vector comparisons.
m: HNSW only. Number of bi-directional links created per new element. Higher can improve recall at the cost of memory.
efConstruction: HNSW only. Index-time candidate list size. Higher can improve index quality but increases indexing time.
efSearch: HNSW only. Query-time candidate list size. Higher can improve recall but slows search.
